Introduction

Daychild is an upcoming 4-member boy group consisting of former WEUS and Black Level Members. They debuted on May 6, 2024, with the single album "Illumination".

'Day' symbolizes a bright and new beginning, and 'Child' means innocence and newness. 'DayChild', comprised of four members Siwoo, K, Roy, and Eden, means "a group as pure and bright as a new day".

On February 18, 2024, BlackBearRecords announced that Roy departed from the group. Due to this, the members will reorganize and then come back, their Rising Star campaign for their debut has been canceled.

On March 12, 2024, Daychild took to Instagram to announce their new member, former Black Level member, Intae.

On December 16, 2024, they took to social media to announce their fandom name. DAYON with the following message: We look forward to the days we will illuminate together.
